panies. Jess is passionate about inclusivity and diversity and was listed on the inaugural Pride in Fintech Power list 2023.\r\n\r\nWe believe that women are not vital only to the future of fintech, but also to the present. And we are excited to celebrate their achievements and contributions today and every day.\r\n\r\nHappy International Women's Day! \\uD83D\\uDC9C\r\n\\uD835\\uDDEA\\uD835\\uDDF2 \\uD835\\uDDF5\\uD835\\uDDEE\\uD835\\uDE03\\uD835\\uDDF2 \\uD835\\uDE00\\uD835\\uDDFC\\uD835\\uDDFA\\uD835\\uDDF2 \\uD835\\uDDF2\\uD835\\uDE05\\uD835\\uDDF0\\uD835\\uDDF6\\uD835\\uDE01\\uD835\\uDDF6\\uD835\\uDDFB\\uD835\\uDDF4 \\uD835\\uDDFB\\uD835\\uDDF2\\uD835\\uDE04\\uD835\\uDE00 \\uD835\\uDE01\\uD835\\uDDFC \\uD835\\uDE00\\uD835\\uDDF5\\uD835\\uDDEE\\uD835\\uDDFF\\uD835\\uDDF2! \\uD83C\\uDF89\\uD83D\\uDE4C\r\n\r\nIt is with great pleasure that The Pitchmark Group announces the creation of its much-anticipated Strategy Team. Since our inception in 2010, we've always believed in innovation and growth, and the creation of this team kicks off our ambitious 2024 goals \\uD83E\\uDD1D\r\n\r\nThis dynamic lineup, consisting of General Manager Claire Phillips (left), Head of Commercial Strategy Matt Bartle (centre), and HR Officer Katie Y. (right), has been assembled to collaborate closely with our Board of Directors in reinforcing our vision, values, and culture and ensuring the successful delivery of our organisational KPIs.\r\n\r\nCentered on principles of integrity, trust, authenticity, equality, and ownership, Bartle is confident that the Group has the ideal individuals committed to achieving the goals, making 2024 'the most exciting yet'.\r\n\r\n\\\r\nProject Manager Richard Beedell is presenting today at the Hydrogen UK Annual Conference & Awards in NCC Birmingham.\r\n\r\nRichard is a chartered chemical engineer with 12 yearsa€™ experience in our industry. Hea€™s leading the delivery of the UKa€™s first hydrogen training course for upskilling existing Gas Safe registered