 the Tigerbite Mini-Crusher to pulverize brick and concrete waste, transforming it into gravel-sized particles that can be reused within various other construction projects. This not only reduces the demand for raw materials but also minimizes the carbon emissions associated with traditional construction practices.\r\nThe demonstration I received upon delivery was unbelievable, I had no idea that our construction waste could be recycled so efficiently. The Tigerbite Mini-Crusher, along with the training courses our students will receive centered around the machine, will make them think about more sustainable choices within their future careers as a builders. I truly believe that the next generation of builders will benefit greatly from this knowledge and will be more conscious of their impact on the environment. The added benefit is that the Construction department will no longer have to pay to have waste removed from the college, it will now be crushed and donated to areas locally where hardcore is required. I have to give a big thankyou to Darren French for all of the advice given!\r\nA \r\n#MiniCrusher #ConcreteCrusher #LandscapingTools #Builders #Renovators #tigerbite425 #tigerbiteminicrusher #Efficiency #sustainability\r\nWas a pleasure having you on site helping us use sustainable materials as and where we can to contribute to helping the environment.\r\n\r\n#groundworks #construction #constructionindustry #sustainability #sustainablematerials #environmentallyfriendly \r\n\r\nCale Phillips\r\nHave you missed our webinar on #Sustainability in #QualityImprovement?\r\n\r\nThe recording is now available on our website: https://lnkd.in/e9VKMfhf\r\n\r\n#Sustainable #SustainableHealthcare #Healthcare #ClimateChange\r\nUnique innovation - the only....\r\n\r\nWatch this space, launching soon - 20/02/2024\r\n\r\n#Construction #Project #Contractors #Architects #FireSafety #Contracting #Cladding #FaA§ade #Facades #CurtainWall #FacadeDesign #BuildingEnvelope #Membrane #Pas