ure solution will help to deliver a step change in the pace of EV charge-point roll out across the North East. We have recently adopted a North East Zero Emission Vehicle Strategy which aims to deliver excellent charging infrastructure in our region, and build better confidence in the people who use it. We were therefore delighted to work with NEPO to design a flexible solution that will help us to deliver our investment pipeline in new electric vehicle charge-points, through a range of high quality suppliers, for the benefit of the North Easta€™s residents, businesses and visitors alike.a€\u009d\r\n\r\nWant to find out more? Read more: https://lnkd.in/eP3hzzek\r\n\r\n#ProcuringForYou #PublicSectorProcurement #EVCharging #EVNews\r\nWhata€™s the difference between R&D tax credits and R&D grants? And how long does it take to get the grant money if successful? \r\n\r\nJust a few questions, Granted Director Jon Williams covered at the recent Innovation Funding and Support Conference in Birmingham. \r\n\r\nJon took to the stage with a panel of speakers to present on one of our favourite topics 'Navigating innovation funding'. \r\n\r\nJon spoke on the following key points: \r\n\r\nR&D tax credits vs R&D grants: \r\n- Notably, R&D tax credits are retrospective as opposed to gaining funding in advance with R&D grants.\r\n\r\nCapital grants vs R&D grants: \r\n- Capital grants are for capital expenditure, typically to stimulate employment and are most often distributed regionally. While R&D grants are for NEW and UNIQUE R&D projects with wider impacts and are typically distributed nationally. \r\n\r\nHow long does it take to get the grant money? \r\n- As a guide, it typically takes between 9-12 months from application to first drawdown of grant funds. Grant funds are typically paid in arrears. \r\n\r\nThe importance of fund matching\r\n- The key to accessing the right grant fund at the right time lies in being a€œgrant-readya€\u009d through early anticipation of likely funds 