s may also be a source of contention. \r\n\r\nThe FCA has aimed to expand on the vague nature of the rule by proposing additional guidance for firms. The expectations for sustainability claims are laid out as follows - they must be:\r\n - Correct and capable of being substantiated\r\n#NOME?\r\n#NOME?\r\n#NOME?\r\n\r\nRegarding the third element, the Guidance document reminds firms that #CMA (Competition and Markets Authority) & #ASA (Advertisement Standards Authority) guidance, the FCA Principles 6 & 7, and the Consumer Duty apply to sustainability claims made at entity-level. It adds that a firm's claims about themselves may be considered part of a 'representative picture' in a decision-making process. \r\n\r\nGiven that net zero targets are easier to set than implement, firms should be aware of this interpretation and have some form of action planned to back this commitment. Worst case scenario, this would help you get your homework done early ahead of planned FCA requirements for Transition Plan Taskforce (#TPT) aligned disclosures. \r\n\r\nLet me know what your views are in the comments!\r\n\r\n#netzero #transitionplans\r\nEmbracing sustainability isn't just good for the planet a€“ it's a smart move for businesses too \\uD83C\\uDF0D\r\n\r\n\\uD83D\\uDCB7 Cost Savings: Recycling cuts waste disposal costs, putting more pounds back into your business.\r\n\r\naœ… Positive Brand Image: Showcasing your commitment to the environment boosts your brand's reputation.\r\n\r\nas–i¸\u008f Legal Compliance: Stay on the right side of the law by adhering to environmental regulations. Avoid fines and embrace green practices!\r\n\r\na™»i¸\u008f Resource Efficiency: Recycling materials means fewer resources used, contributing to a more efficient and sustainable supply chain.\r\n\r\nLet's make a positive impact on the environment and the bottom line.\r\n\r\n#SustainableBusiness #CostSavings #LegalCompliance #CorporateResponsibility\r\n\\uD83C\\uDF86 Happy New Year from Crumbs Brewi